A fun place to go based on the original & charming atmosphere. Waitstaff will not disappoint with quirky personality, jokes, & fun "attitude". Burgers are cooked in a vertical cast-iron grill, they come on white toast with the option of: cheese, onion, tomato and are served on a paper plate. House-made potato salad and small bags of chips available for sides. Connecticut's own Foxon Park sodas are available in bottles and other big name sodas in cans. You may not have any ketchup. The Library of Congress recognizes Louis' Lunch as "the birthplace of the hamburger sandwich".
